<!DOCTYPE html
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>ELH - Bash example</title>
    </head> 
    <style>
        red {
            color: red;
        }
        blu {
            color: cyan;
        }
        ora {
            color: orange;
        }
        pin {
            color: magenta;
        }
        gre {
            color: green;
        }
        yel {
            color: yellow;
        }

        code {
            background-color: black;
            color: orange;
            padding: 0.25em;
            border-radius: 0.25em;
        }

        pre:has(code) {
            background-color: #151515;
            color: lime;
            padding: 0.5em 0.75em;
            border-radius: 0.35em;
            border: 0.1em solid #333333;
            width: 50vw;
            code {
                color: unset;
                background-color: transparent;
                padding: unset;
            }
        }
    </style>
    <body>
        <h1>ELH Markdown example</h1>
        <p>Renders the following Markdown on the server, similar to PHP</p>
<pre><code><pin># Foo</pin>
<gre>## bar</gre>
<yel>### baz</yel>
<blu>- qux</blu>
<blu>- quux</blu>
  <ora>- quuz</ora>

<pin>`corge`</pin>

<red>```</red>
<red>grault</red>
<red>```</red></code></pre>
    
        <p>The output:</p>
        <$md
# Foo
## bar
### baz
- qux
- quux
  - quuz

`corge`

```
grault
```
          $>
    </body>
</html>

